#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:1
msgid "pyemscripten_2024_0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:3
msgid ""
"By default, all builds of the Pyodide runtime with Python 3.12 will use the "
"`pyemscripten_2024_0` platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:7
msgid "Prior to {pep}`783`, the platform was referenced as `pyodide_2024_0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:10
msgid "ABI Specification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:12
msgid "CPython and Emscripten Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:14
msgid "**CPython**: 3.12"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:15
msgid "**Emscripten**: 3.1.58"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:17
msgid "WASM_BIGINT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:19
msgid "All shared libraries must be linked with `-sWASM_BIGINT`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:21
msgid ""
"Since Rust 1.84.0 or nightly 2024-11-05, Rust will automatically pass `-"
"Clink-arg=-sWASM_BIGINT`. In earlier versions of Rust it was required to "
"pass `-Clink-arg=-sWASM_BIGINT` explicitly. Passing it explicitly will work "
"in all cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:26
msgid "Unwinding ABIs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:28
msgid ""
"By default, C++ libraries are built with exceptions disabled, and `throw` is "
"an abort. The same is true for `setjmp`/`longjmp`. To enable exceptions and "
"`setjmp`/`longjmp`, `-fexceptions` must be passed at compile time and link "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:32
msgid "Rust will automatically enable unwinding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:34
msgid "Rust Toolchain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:36
msgid ""
"The Rust toolchain used must be a nightly released prior to October 1st 2025."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:38
msgid "Runtime Library Loading Path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/312.md:40
msgid ""
"Specifying an RPATH is not supported, `emcc` will warn and ignore it. The "
"dynamic loader has been patched so that all dynamic libraries in a wheel "
"named `wheel_name-<tag>.whl` will be loaded as if `/lib/python3.12/site-"
"packages/wheel_name.libs` is on the `RPATH`, so any dynamic library "
"dependencies should be placed in the wheel in a folder called `wheel_name."
"libs`."
msgstr ""

